# Conventions

## Naming

| Thing | File | Symbol | Example |
|-------|------|--------|---------|
| API route | `route.ts` in folder | `GET`, `POST`, `PATCH`, `DELETE` | `src/app/api/documents/route.ts` |
| Server page | `page.tsx` | default export | `DashboardPage` |
| Client component | `PascalCase.tsx` | named export | `DashboardClient` |
| Lib module | `kebab or single word.ts` | named functions | `getDocumentAccess` |
| Zod schema | `*Schema` | `loginSchema` | `src/lib/validation.ts` |
| Test | `*.test.ts` next to source | `describe` / `it` | `validation.test.ts` |
| TipTap extension | `custom-extensions.ts` | `Extension.create` | `FontSize` |

## Imports

- **Always** use `@/` alias (`@/lib/auth`, `@/components/...`)
- **Never** deep relative imports across layers (`../../lib/...`)
- No barrel `index.ts` files — import from concrete paths

## Patterns

```typescript
// API route handler shape
export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  const session = await getSession();
  if (!session) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Unauthorized" }, { status: 401 });
  const parsed = someSchema.safeParse(await request.json());
  if (!parsed.success) return NextResponse.json({ error: "..." }, { status: 400 });
  // prisma + return
}

// Client component
"use client";
export function Foo({ initialData }: { initialData: ... }) { ... }
```

## Forbidden

- ❌ `any` — use explicit types or `unknown` + narrow
- ❌ Default exports in `src/lib/**` (components/pages use default where Next requires)
- ❌ `prisma` in `src/components/**`
- ❌ Raw SQL — use Prisma client only
- ❌ Committing `.env` — use `.env.example`
